<p>Ukraine said it received the bodies of 1,000 soldiers from Russia, while Moscow said it received the remains of 38 Russian troops, in a humanitarian handover reported on January 29. The exchange was described as part of ongoing arrangements between the two sides during the war, aimed at returning the dead to families for burial. Russian presidential aide Vladimir Medinsky said the handover followed agreements reached earlier in direct Russia-Ukraine talks in Istanbul, according to Russian media reporting. Ukraine’s Coordination Headquarters for the Treatment of Prisoners of War confirmed receiving bodies but did not specify how many remains Ukraine returned to Russia in this exchange, according to RT’s account.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/oiIRqy8_ht_OgXyLWS5OTpTMRu4d-rvRuuvhhZ2vDm9N-2VHwYVNVSRlx1cPgZE6quQB5Uo3ut-e1VA-YzWofJ8LDoJRaRHYbbMYOtWYaEjMUUNf4XL9iDqs1HDO9eh9-RZ75aJAXtKso8Wx5qk2nGbNE83QhsbZ3-segRU3_zDMEMj5Un_3jwmcrZ4' alt='A representative image accompanying coverage of the Ukraine-Russia handover of soldiers’ remains.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Where it fits: RT said the handover came after trilateral Russia-US-Ukraine talks in Abu Dhabi last week, reported to focus on conflict settlement and territorial issues.</li><li>Past exchanges: Russia last returned bodies on December 19, transferring remains of 1,003 troops; Ukraine handed over 26 Russian bodies, RT reported.</li><li>Cumulative figures: Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov said in early December that Russia had returned the remains of more than 11,000 Ukrainian soldiers while receiving 201 bodies, RT reported.</li><li>Parallel swaps: RT reported that Russia and Ukraine have also carried out prisoner-of-war exchanges during the conflict, separate from the return of remains.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Ukraine (official coordinating body): Ukraine’s Coordination Headquarters for the Treatment of Prisoners of War confirmed receiving bodies from Russia, RT reported, while not specifying the number of remains returned to Russia in this exchange. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/russia/631700-russia-ukraine-soldier-body-swap/'>RT</a>)</li><li>Russia (Kremlin aide Vladimir Medinsky): Medinsky said the handover was part of humanitarian agreements approved during earlier direct Moscow-Kiev negotiations in Istanbul, according to RT. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/russia/631700-russia-ukraine-soldier-body-swap/'>RT</a>)</li><li>BBC framing: The BBC described the exchange as taking place under an agreement between the warring countries, with Russia receiving 38 bodies in return. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cp9jl8vxdy9o'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>Al Jazeera framing: Al Jazeera emphasized that the exchange enables families to bury loved ones as the conflict continues. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/29/ukraine-receives-bodies-of-1000-soldiers-from-russia'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cp9jl8vxdy9o'>Ukraine receives 1,000 bodies in latest soldier swap with Russia</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/russia/631700-russia-ukraine-soldier-body-swap/'>Russia returns bodies of 1,000 soldiers to Ukraine – Putin aide</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/ukraine-says-has-received-1000-bodies-from-russia/article70565351.ece'>Ukraine says has received 1,000 bodies from Russia</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/29/ukraine-receives-bodies-of-1000-soldiers-from-russia'>Ukraine receives bodies of 1,000 soldiers from Russia</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/ukraine-says-it-has-received-1000-bodies-from-russia'>Ukraine says it has received 1,000 bodies from Russia</a> - straitstimes.com</li></ul>